verbose_text: As evidenced by increased levels of phosphorylated ATF2, TNF-alpha concentration-dependently induced the p38 MAPK activity, which was concentration-dependently decreased by WIN-55; the inhibitory effect of WIN-55 was largely blocked by JTE907 but not MJ15 (XREF_FIG).
evidence: p38 MAPK activity, which was concentration-dependently decreased by WIN-55
